# Example of the "@dataset" directive (draft §3.4.4).
#
# Many instances of a single message type in a single document. Each row
# binds positionally to the header column list; the three cell states
# (empty = absent, `null` = present-but-null, value = present) carry the
# same semantics as the PXF annotations of §6.1.
#
# Schema reference: test.v1.AllTypes (see testdata/test.proto).

@dataset test.v1.AllTypes (string_field, int32_field, enum_field, ts_field, nullable_int)

("row-1", 1, STATUS_ACTIVE,   2026-05-11T10:00:00Z, 42)
("row-2", 2, STATUS_INACTIVE, 2026-05-11T10:00:01Z, null)
("row-3", 3, STATUS_ACTIVE,   2026-05-11T10:00:02Z, )
( ,      4, STATUS_ACTIVE,   2026-05-11T10:00:03Z, 99)
